{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = AFF stadium | nickname = | image = | location = [[Kabul]], {{AFG}} | broke_ground = | opened = September 18, 2012 | closed = | demolished = | operator = | surface = Artificial turf | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = All clubs of the [[Afghan Premier League]] | seating_capacity = 5,000 }}
The '''Afghanistan Football Federation stadium''' is a football stadium in [[Kabul]], [[Afghanistan]] and competition venue of all Clubs of the new [[Afghan Premier League]]. The AFF stadium has a capacity of 5,000, and the surface is of [[Artificial turf]].
