'''Boston River''' is a sports club located in [[Montevideo]], [[Uruguay]]. Their main focus is on [[association football|football]], currently playing in the [[Uruguayan Primera División]]. At the [[futsal]] league of [[Uruguayan Football Association|AUF]], Boston River compete in the first division.

The club is named after a tailor shop owned by its founder, called "Sastrería Boston", and [[Argentine Primera División|Argentine side]] [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]].

