The '''Cambodian national cricket team''' is a cricket team that represents the nation of [[Cambodia]] in international cricket competitions and is administered by the [[Cricket Association of Cambodia]].

Cambodia applied for [[Asian Cricket Council]] membership, which was granted in 2012.<ref>[http://www.asiancricket.org/index.php/news/july-2012/2462 NEW ACC MEMBERS: CAMBODIA, CHINESE TAIPEI AND TAJIKISTAN] Asian Cricket Council. Retrieved 29 October 2012</ref> The Cricket Association also plans to apply for membership of the National Olympic Committee.

Cricket in the former French colony of Cambodia is still a mainly expatriate game at senior level, and a growing interest with the younger set of boys that play. Additionally, a structured cricket league is being planned in the country with the help of the [[Thailand Cricket League]] and that the [[Olympic Stadium (Phnom Penh)|National Stadium, Phnom Penh]] and Army Stadium will be available. Cambodia is planned to host the [[2023 Southeast Asian Games]] and a cricket ground could be funded and built.<ref>[http://www.asiancricket.org/index.php/news/october-2012/2509 CAMBODIA COMING ON] Asian Cricket Council. Retrieved 29 October 2012</ref> A cricket ground 10km from the capital began construction and was expected to be ready by October 2014.<ref name=CGG>[http://www.asiancricket.org/index.php/news/april-2014/2874 "Cambodia Gets Going"], Asian Cricket Council. Retrieved 10 March 2016</ref>

The Cricket Association planned to join the [[International Cricket Council]] as an Affiliate Member in 2013,<ref>[http://www.icc-cricket.com/newsdetails.php?newsId=21862_1350552540 Cambodia taking first steps] International Cricket Council. Retrieved 29 October 2012 {{deadlink|date=March 2016}}</ref> but in 2014 it was reported that this was some way in the future yet.<ref name=CGG />

