{{Infobox National Olympic Committee | title = Egyptian Olympic Committee | logo = Egyptian Olympic Committee Logo.png | size = 150px | country = Egypt | code = EGY | created = 1910 in [[Khedivate of Egypt]] | recognized = 1910 | association = ANOCA | headquarters = [[Cairo]], [[Egypt]] | president = [[Hesham Mohamed Tawfeq Hatab]] | secretary general = [[Alaa Gabr]] | website = [http://www.egyptianolympic.org/ www.egyptianolympic.org] }} The '''Egyptian Olympic Committee''' ({{lang-ar|اللجنة الأولمبية المصرية}}, abbreviated as '''EOC''') is a [[non-profit organization]] serving as the [[National Olympic Committee]] of [[Egypt]] and a part of the [[International Olympic Committee]].
==History== Egyptian Olympic Committee was founded during the [[Khedivate of Egypt]] on 13 June 1910 in [[Alexandria]] by the Angelo Bolanaki, first egyptian athlete who participated in international sport competitions outside country. Egypt first appeared in the [[1912 Summer Olympics|1912 Stockholm Olympic Games]] with one athlete in fencing. It was the 14th country to join the [[IOC]].<ref>[http://www.egyptianolympic.org/history.html History of Egyptian Olympic Committee on official site]</ref>
