{{infobox country at games | NOC = FIJ | NOCname = [[Fiji Association of Sports and National Olympic Committee]] | games = Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games | year = 2017 | date = 17–27 September | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = {{url|http://www.fijiolympiccommittee.com/}} | location = [[Ashgabat]] | competitors = 28 | sports = 4 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 1 | silver = 1 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Fiji]]''' competed at the [[2017 Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games]] held in [[Ashgabat]], [[Turkmenistan]]. 28 athletes competed in 4 different sports. Fijian team won 2 medals including one gold and a silver medal in the Games.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ashgabat2017.com/results/fij|title=Fiji {{!}} The 5th Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games - 2017|last=|first=|date=|website=ashgabat2017.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ocasia.org/Game/GameParticular.aspx?9QoyD9QEWPdkzAjI/K7uyA==|title=Olympic Council of Asia : Games|website=www.ocasia.org|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref>
Fiji also made its first appearance at an [[Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games]] event along with other [[Oceania]] nations including [[Australia at the 2017 Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games|Australia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fijitimes.com/story.aspx?id=416406|title=2017 Asian Indoor and Martial Arts Games: Team Fiji anticipate adequate rest - Fiji Times Online|website=www.fijitimes.com|language=en|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fijisun.com.fj/2017/10/02/happy-to-be-in-5-finals-buadromo/|title=Happy To Be In 5 Finals: Buadromo {{!}} Fiji Sun|website=fijisun.com.fj|language=en-US|access-date=2017-10-11}}</ref>
