The '''Himachal Pradesh Handball Association''' ('''HPHA''') is an organisation which manages and controls the sport of [[Handball]] in the [[India]]n state of [[Himachal Pradesh]].
==About== {{Infobox national sports federations | name = Himachal Pradesh Handball Association | abbr = (HPHA) | logo = | logosize = px200 | url = | sport = [[Handball]] | founded = | IF = | IF_abbr = | IF_joined = | continental_assoc = | regional_games= | president = Mr. '''[Bharat Sahni]]'''{{flagicon|India}} | sectitle = Headquarters | address1 = [[Himachal Pradesh]] | country = [[India]] | secretary_general = Mr. Nand Kishore Sharma | staff_pos1 = | staff_name1 = | staff_pos2 = | staff_name2 = | sponsors = }} The '''Himachal Pradesh Handball Association''' ('''HPHA''') is an organisation which govern and control the sport of [[handball]] in the state of [[Himachal Pradesh]]. '''HPHA''' is affiliated to [[Handball Federation of India]]. Team selected by the '''HPHA''' take part in National Championship held under the aegis of the [[Handball Federation of India]]. Himachal Pradesh Women And Junior Girls teams are currently Silver Medalists of National Championships.
