{{Infobox Golf Facility |golf_facility_name = Jumeirah Golf Estates |image = |location = {{flagicon|UAE}} [[Dubai]], [[UAE]] |establishment = 2009 |type = Private |owner = Jumeirah Golf Estates |operator = <!-- name of organization/company --> |holes = 72 |tournaments = [[DP World Tour Championship, Dubai]] |website = [http://www.jumeirahgolfestates.com/ www.jumeirahgolfestates.com] |course1 = Fire |designer1 = Greg Norman |par1 = |length1 = yards |course2 = Earth |designer2 = Greg Norman |par2 = 72 |length2 = 7,675 yards |record2 = 62; [[Justin Rose]], (2012) }} '''Jumeirah Golf Estates''' is a luxury residential [[golf]] community that is located along [[E 311 road (United Arab Emirates)]], in [[Dubai]], [[United Arab Emirates]].
Each [[golf course]] is to have a different environmental theme &ndash; Fire, Earth &ndash; and were designed by [[Greg Norman]].
The Norman designed Earth Course is the venue for the [[DP World Tour Championship, Dubai]], the season ending tournament on the [[European Tour]].
