{{distinguish|Nurul Aleshahnezan Nordin}} {{Malay name|Nurrul Aleshahnezan|Metali}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Nurrul Aleshanezan | fullname = Awangku Nurrul Aleshahnezan bin Pengiran Metali | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|01|21|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Brunei]] | height = | position = [[Midfielder]], [[Defender (association football)|Defender]] | currentclub = ''Unattached'' | clubnumber = | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2007–2010 | caps1 = | goals1 = | clubs1 = [[NBT FC]] | years2 = 2011–2013 | caps2 = | goals2 = | clubs2 = [[Majra FC]] | years3 = 2014–2016 | caps3 = | goals3 = 2| clubs3 = [[Indera SC]] | nationalyears1= 2005 | nationalcaps1= | nationalgoals1= | nationalteam1= [[Brunei national under-16 football team|Brunei U16]] | nationalyears2= 2005 | nationalcaps2= | nationalgoals2= | nationalteam2= [[Brunei national under-20 football team|Brunei U20]] | nationalyears3= 2007 | nationalcaps3= 3 | nationalgoals3= 0 | nationalteam3= [[Brunei national under-21 football team|Brunei U21]] | nationalyears4= 2008 | nationalcaps4= 2 | nationalgoals4= 0 | nationalteam4= [[Brunei national football team|Brunei]] | nationalyears5= 2011 | nationalcaps5= 3 | nationalgoals5= 0 | nationalteam5= [[Brunei national under-23 football team|Brunei U23]] | club-update = 22 May 2017 | ntupdate = 9 August 2017 }}
'''[[Malay styles and titles#Brunei|Awangku]] Nurrul Aleshahnezan bin [[Malay styles and titles#Brunei|Pengiran]] Metali''' (born 21 January 1989) is a [[Brunei]]an [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] or [[Defender (association football)|defender]].<ref>{{cite web |title=LUCKY WIN FOR INDERA SC |url=http://inderasportsclub-media.blogspot.com/2015/09/lucky-win-for-indera-sc.html|date=8 September 2015|publisher=The Brunei Times|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref> He appeared twice for the [[Brunei national football team]] in 2008.
Aleshahnezan first played league football for [[NBT FC]] in the [[Brunei Premier League]] from [[2007–08 Brunei Premier League|2007]] to [[2009–10 Brunei Premier League|2010]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Brunei 2009/10|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/brunei09.html|date=14 March 2013|publisher=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref> Afterwards he moved to [[Majra FC]] after the conclusion of the [[2011 Southeast Asian Games]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Majra FC move to second in DST Super League|url=http://msabdbft.blogspot.com/2013/01/majra-fc-move-to-second-in-dst-super.html|date=6 January 2013|publisher=The Brunei Times|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref> He switched clubs to [[Indera SC]] for the [[2014 Brunei Super League]] season,<ref>{{cite web |title=PLAYER PROFILE (2014) |url=http://inderasportsclub.blogspot.com/2013/09/football-team.html|date=|publisher=Indera SC|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref> and stayed there for three years, winning the championship in his first year.<ref>{{cite web |title=Indera SC repeat as champs |url=http://bruneifootball.blogspot.com/2014/09/indera-sc-repeat-as-champs.html|date=3 September 2014|publisher=The Brunei Times|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref>
==International career== Aleshahnezan played for Brunei [[Brunei national under-16 football team|under-16s]] at the [[2005 Lion City Cup|2005]] [[Lion City Cup]], then the [[2005 AFF U-20 Youth Championship]] held in [[Singapore]] and [[Indonesia]] respectively.<ref>{{cite web |title=20th Lion City Cup (2005)|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesl/lioncity-u1618-05.html|date=7 September 2006|publisher=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.suaramerdeka.com/harian/0508/08/ora04.htm|title=Indonesia Tampil Beda|publisher=Suara Merdeka|date=8 August 2005|accessdate=9 August 2017}}</ref> He then played three games for the [[Brunei national under-21 football team|under-21s]] at the [[2007 Hassanal Bolkiah Trophy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hassanalbolkiahtrophy.com.bn/?page_id=251|title=Brunei Darussalam|publisher=Information Department, Prime Minister's Office of Brunei|date=7 February 2007|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20121231201512/www.hassanalbolkiahtrophy.com.bn/?page_id=251|archivedate=31 December 2012|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref> He made his international debut for the [[Brunei national football team|national team]] at the [[2008 AFC Challenge Cup qualification]] matches held in the [[Philippines]]. He played twice in that tournament, against the [[Philippines national football team|home side]] and also [[Bhutan national football team|Bhutan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://images.the-afc.com/Documents/competitions/fixtures/252-1497.pdf|title=MATCH SUMMARY: BRUNEI DARUSSALAM 0 - 1 PHILIPPINES|publisher=Asian Football Confederation|date=13 May 2008|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080704071945/http://images.the-afc.com/Documents/competitions/fixtures/252-1497.pdf|archivedate=4 July 2008|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://images.the-afc.com/Documents/competitions/fixtures/252-1495.pdf|title=MATCH SUMMARY: BHUTAN 1 - 1 BRUNEI DARUSSALAM|publisher=Asian Football Confederation|date=15 May 2008|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080704072216/http://images.the-afc.com/Documents/competitions/fixtures/252-1495.pdf|archivedate=4 July 2008|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref>
Three years later, Aleshahnezan travelled with the [[Brunei national under-23 football team|national under-23 team]] to [[Indonesia]] for the [[2011 Southeast Asian Games|26th SEA Games]], at a time when Brunei was just recovering from a two-year exile from international football.<ref>{{cite web |title=INFORMASI LENGKAP DARI SKUAD SUKAN SEA|url=http://profbola-soccer.blogspot.com/2011/10/informasi-lengkap-dari-skuad-sukan-sea.html|date=31 October 2011|publisher=Jabar Isnin|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref> He started in the only victory for the Young Wasps, a 2-1 win over the [[Philippines national under-23 football team|Philippines]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Brunei playing for pride|url=http://www.bruneiolympic.org/?t=news/index&p=news/2011/20111115e|date=15 November 2011|publisher=The Brunei Times|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref>
==Honours== ;Indera SC *[[Brunei Super League]]: [[2014 Brunei Super League|2014]] *[[Brunei Super Cup|Piala Sumbangsih]]: 2015
==Personal life== Aleshahnezan's brothers are also footballers. Elder brother Aleshahfezan is a player for [[Jerudong FC]],<ref>{{cite web |title=BIG WIN FOR AH UNITED AND WIJAYA FC|url=http://www.aseanfootball.org/v2/2008/03/big-win-for-ah-united-and-wijaya-fc/|date=11 March 2008|publisher=ASEAN Football Federation|accessdate=24 March 2017}}</ref> while younger brothers [[Jumatatul Aleshahrezan Metali|Jumatatul Aleshahrezan]] and Iddzaham Aleshahmezan play for Brunei's under-19 and under-15 squads respectively.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tabuan U-17 menang besar|url=http://mediapermata.com.bn/tabuan-u-17-menang-besar/|date=13 August 2016|publisher=Borneo Bulletin|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web |title=Brunei Juniors Thumped by Malaysia Panthers|url=https://www.brudirect.com/news.php?id=20064|date=15 December 2016|publisher=Borneo Bulletin|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref>
He is currently a futsal coach for youths at [[Kampong Meragang]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Jaga kebersihan, pelihara prasarana kerajaan|url=http://mediapermata.com.bn/jaga-kebersihan-pelihara-prasarana-kerajaan/|date=10 December 2016|publisher=Media Permata|accessdate=24 May 2017}}</ref>
